The paper presents an algorithm for active visual search for mobile robots, which involves both visual attention techniques and decision-making algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as it deals with mobile robots. Additionally, the paper uses visual sensors and attention models, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of decision-making algorithms and the evaluation of performance enhancements suggest that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the fact that the paper deals with mobile robots and their control suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
